We used 6328’s AllianceFlipUtil as a base to allow us to flip the zones to the other side of the field depending on current alliance. mainbot-2025/src/main/java/frc/lib/AllianceFlipUtil.java at develop · FRC-Team-4143/mainbot-2025 · GitHub

I do agree that for this use case the usage of zones was excessive, but it was a fun project and something the students could talk about well to the judges. We used the zone structure to do more advanced context switching during tele-op so we could have a single align button that preforms different scoring/pickup actions based on field location. image 1920×942 70.5 KB

